'''Badgini''' (also spelled '''Bajini''') was a [[sultanate]] on the island of [[Grande Comore]]. It was independent until 1886, when [[Said Ali bin Said Omar of Grande Comore|Sultan Said Ali bin Said Omar]] of [[Sultanate of Bambao|Bambao]] made it a part of the unified [[Ngazidja]] Sultanate. It was ruled by the M'Dombozi clan.



