The '''Boreas Plain''' is an [[abyssal]] plain in the South of [[Fram Strait]] with water depths of around 3 [[km]] at {{coord|78|N|0|E|display=inline,title}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fram Strait Bathymetry |url=http://www.awi.de/en/research/research_divisions/geosciences/marine_geology_and_paleontology/research_themes/bathymetry_and_geodesy/bathymetric_chart_of_the_fram_strait_bcfs/fram_strait_bathymetry/ |publisher=Alfred Wegener Institute for Polar- and Marine Research |accessdate=2 October 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130514200320/http://www.awi.de/en/research/research_divisions/geosciences/marine_geology_and_paleontology/research_themes/bathymetry_and_geodesy/bathymetric_chart_of_the_fram_strait_bcfs/fram_strait_bathymetry/ |archivedate=14 May 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Thiede|first=Jörn|author2=Pfirman, Stephanie |author3=Schenke, Hans-Werner |author4= Reil, Wolfgang |title=Bathymetry of Molloy Deep: Fram Strait between Svalbard and Greenland|journal=Marine Geophysical Researches|year=1990|volume=12|issue=3|pages=197–214|doi=10.1007/BF02266713|url=http://www.springerlink.com/content/e27855w420412527/|publisher=Springer}}</ref>

